A nice Mario inspired Retro Platformer with the following pros and cons:

+ Nice gameplay;
+ Colourful worlds that remind me of [i]Oozi: Earth Adventure[/i];
+ Okay boss fights

- Too slow-paced sometimes, especially under water;
- Score system: (1) earn 1 star per level while defeating all enemies in that level = ruining the flow (2) The 3 secret stars (per level) are sometimes hidden in such a way, that you need to consume or waste so much time to find your way to them, while not always being able to find a clue = trial-and-error involved
- I didn't find any targets in Time Attack Mode. so it's basically just: finish all levels again and get your achievement. You could try to finish a level very fast, but what's the point? Well, maybe to get a nice ranking in the Steam leaderboards.

7/10

